CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 29, 1956, pg. A1, reads: "Annual Yule Event - About 200 youngsters received candy and gifts at the 15th annual Christmas party of Gaines Funeral Home on Christmas Day.  Mrs. Julia B. Gaines, proprietor, hands out the goodies, while assistant manager Harry Spriggs chats with the kids in line to receive their Yuletide gifts. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Harry Briggs standing beside doorway with boys and girls holding boxes of candy, for annual Christmas party at Gaines Funeral home, vertical format
